article.headline: Maine 58, Dartmouth 52
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- David Dubois scored a game-high 17 points for Maine as it held on for a 58-52 win over Dartmouth on Monday night. Dubois had 11 points in the first half as Maine (2-2) built a 39-31 lead at the break. Trailing 53-40, with 5:48 to play, Dartmouth (1-2) reduced the margin to three, 55-52, when Steve Callahan banged in a 3-pointer with 1:51 on the clock. That capped a 12-2 Dartmouth run that included six points by Calvin Arnold. Maine's Ernest Turner made three of four free throws in the final 1:27 to seal the win.
